[cholesterol, dl, level, mg, mmol]

- Cholesterol is a structural component of cell membranes;
- It participates in the production of anti-stress hormones and female and male sex hormones (androgens – such as testosterone; estrogens; progestogens – such as estradiol and progesterone);
- Cholesterol facilitates the synthesis of Vitamin D3 (a cholesterol derivative in the skin transforms into Vitamin D3 under the influence of sunlight);
- It aids in the digestion of fats and the elimination of toxins.

Valuable olive oil – lowers blood pressure and bad cholesterol

Fresh, cold-pressed olive oil has a positive effect on the cardiovascular system, inhibits inflammatory processes, and has anti-cancer properties. The miraculous health benefits of olive oil have been known for centuries.

[cholesterol, concentration, LDL, diet, disease] 

What should an average person with high LDL do? First and foremost: 
- change the ratio of animal-based fats (saturated) to plant-based fats (rapeseed oil, olive oil, etc.); 
- replace sausages and pork neck with chicken and fish; 
- swap chips and fries for nuts and whole-grain bread; 
- appropriate physical activity is also invaluable! 

A study by British scientists found that individuals who not only have high cholesterol but also high body mass can effectively reduce it by losing a few kilograms.
